Customer Segmentation Using Clustering
1. Introduction
Customer Segmentation is the process of dividing customers into different groups based on their purchasing behavior and income. It helps businesses understand customer needs and create targeted marketing strategies. In this project, K-Means Clustering is used to group customers with similar characteristics.

2. Objective
    • To analyze customer data. 
    • To group customers into different segments. 
    • To identify high-value and low-value customers. 
    • To improve marketing and business decision-making. 

3. System Modules
Module 1: Data Collection
    • Collect customer dataset from CSV files. 
    • Dataset contains customer income and spending information. 
Module 2: Data Preprocessing
    • Load dataset using Pandas. 
    • Handle missing values. 
    • Select required attributes. 
Module 3: Feature Selection
Selected features:
    • Income 
    • MntWines 
    • MntMeatProducts 
    • MntGoldProds 
Module 4: Clustering Module
    • Apply K-Means Clustering algorithm. 
