5. Methodology
Step 1: Data Collection
    • Import customer dataset from CSV file. 
Step 2: Data Preprocessing
    • Remove missing values. 
    • Prepare data for clustering. 
Step 3: Feature Selection
Choose important features:
    • Income 
    • MntWines 
    • MntMeatProducts 
    • MntGoldProds 
Step 4: K-Means Clustering
    • Apply K-Means algorithm. 
    • Divide customers into 3 groups. 
Step 5: Visualization
    • Generate scatter plot. 
    • Display customer segments. 
Step 6: Result Generation
    • Save clustered data into output CSV file. 

6. Algorithm
K-Means Clustering Algorithm
    1. Select the number of clusters (K). 
    2. Initialize cluster centroids. 
    3. Assign customers to the nearest centroid. 
    4. Update centroid positions. 
    5. Repeat until centroids do not change. 
    6. Form final customer segments. 
Conclusion
Customer Segmentation Using Clustering is an effective technique for analyzing customer behavior. By applying K-Means Clustering, customers are grouped into meaningful segments, enabling businesses to improve marketing strategies, customer satisfaction, and overall business performance.
